a pub landlord who was convicted of drink driving after claiming he was sleepwalking and was not drunk has vowed to never drink again. James Boase, landlord of the Coppa Dolla pub in Broadhempston, Devon had been drinking with a friend in Torquay on March 13, 2014. the last thing he could remember was going to bed at approximately 12.30am and then awoke beside his car which had been involved in a car crash.